category: Devel Libs Math
requires: cygwin libisl6
external-source: isl
sdesc: "Integer set library (development)"
ldesc: "isl is a library for manipulating sets and relations of integer points
bounded by linear constraints. Supported operations on sets include
intersection, union, set difference, emptiness check, convex hull, (integer)
affine hull, integer projection, and computing the lexicographic minimum using
parametric integer programming. It also includes an ILP solver based on
generalized basis reduction. isl is released under LGPLv2.1"
